
[1]hydrate

   HY'DRATE, n. [Gr. water.] In chimistry, a compound, indefinite
   proportions, of a metallic oxyd with water.

   A hydrate is a substance which has formed so intimate a union with
   water as to solidify it, and render it a component part.

   Slaked lime is a hydrate of lime.
